title: Number of M & A transactions in Asia 2015 - 2017 , by country
summary: This grouped bar chart shows SOME LABEL on the Y-axis for 9 different Quarters for 4 groups Australia, China/Hong Kong, India, and Japan that are presented on the X-axis.
All through the Quarters, the SOME LABEL for India have climbed. On the other hand, for China/Hong Kong the SOME LABEL have reduced.
Out of all 4 groups, China/Hong Kong had the highest SOME LABEL in Quarter Q4 2016 and India had the lowest SOME LABEL in Quarter Q3 2017.
Among all the Quarters, India had the highest SOME LABEL 286.0 in Quarter Q1 2016 and lowest value 156.0 in Quarter Q3 2017.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart represents 9 different Quarters on X-axis for 4 groups Australia, China/Hong Kong, India, and Japan. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding SOME LABEL.
All through the Quarters, the SOME LABEL for India have climbed. On the other hand, for China/Hong Kong the SOME LABEL have reduced.
In Quarter Q4 2016, China/Hong Kong had the highest SOME LABEL 1059.0 among the 4 groups and in Q3 2017, India had the lowest SOME LABEL 156.0.
In Quarter Q1 2016, India had the highest SOME LABEL among all 9 Quarters and it has the lowest SOME LABEL in Quarter Q3 2017.
Quarter Q1 2016 and Q3 2017 had the biggest gap of 130.0 between the highest and lowest SOME LABEL found for India.
Among all 4 groups, China/Hong Kong had the gap of 327.0 between the maximum and minimum SOME LABEL observed in Quarter Q4 2016 and Q2 2016 respectively.
China/Hong Kong had the maximum SOME LABEL out of all 4 groups in Quarter Q4 2016 followed by China/Hong Kong in Q4 2016, and the minimum SOME LABEL is found for India in Q3 2017.
On average, the Quarter Q4 2016 had the highest SOME LABEL for all 4 groups Australia, China/Hong Kong, India, and Japan. Whereas Q2 2016 had the lowest average SOME LABEL.
